2. Determine the radius and circumference of a half-full balloon. The volume of a sphere is (4/3)πr 3 so if the radius is halved, the volume is reduced to one-eighth the original volume. For half the volume, the radius of the balloon should be reduced by approximately 20% or be about 0.8 times the radius of the full balloon. Using this information, determine the circumference of a half-full balloon.
